reviews.review_text: A wealth of Viola Lee Blues & more I have compared this with the nearly identical Viola Lee Blues Rehearsals dated ??/??/66, source #18846 (Uli Teute and Hanno Bunjes). This recent recording sounds like it has NR and seems muffled in comparison to #18846. Sure like the two tracks of Cardboard Cowboy on this. A great historical recording.

Before their trip down south Bear was doing the sound at the Questing Beast and he accompanied the Dead down to Los Angeles shortly after this recording. Dennis McNally's book is great for info on these shows and the trip to LA.

These rehearsals are nice to listen to for a fly-on-the-wall of the boys working through Viola and Phil's Cardboard Cowboy.
